Optimize performance of ``PyLinter``.``_discover_files()`` traversal
of a directory tree during startup. This is done by telling
``os.walk()`` to do things in a top-down fashion, and properly
removing ignored directories from the dirnames list so that those
subtrees are not traversed. In Pylint, this reduced by ~= 81% the
number of directories of what would otherwise be traversed. Bigger
projects could see even greater reductions.

Closes #11005
